            "text": "{Maybe.  I think that would depend on how readily the problem at hand is parallelized, and how well Ruby and Java in particular are at taking advantage of the parallelization inherent to the problem.  As languages go, they certainly are poorly designed for it... but I can see how \"Java and Ruby advocates\" wouldn't solve that by switching to a better language for parallelization.  And extra CPUs will never help for problems of indirection across large network connections or deep indirections against a slow hard disk.}",
            "id": "24433ef43767ef86eb28f71ecdb77507"
